# Coding Rules

## Clarity
- Prefer simple, readable code over clever solutions
- Avoid unnecessary abstraction
- Use descriptive names

## Structure
- Keep functions small and single-purpose
- Keep files focused and modular
- Group related logic together

## Interfaces
- Use explicit inputs and outputs
- Use types where possible
- Avoid hidden side effects

## Error Handling
- Validate inputs at boundaries
- Fail early with clear, actionable errors

## Consistency
- Follow existing project patterns and conventions
- Do not introduce new patterns without clear justification

## Observability
- Add logs where debugging would be difficult
- Avoid excessive or noisy logging

## AI Behavior
- Treat generated code as a draft, not final
- Make minimal, targeted changes
- Do not refactor unrelated code

